The term &quot;Voldemort&quot; means absolutely nothing to Kaucky and the only term he correctly guessed during the test was &quot;the largest golf hole in Prague&quot;.
&quot;That&#39;s the Tunnel Blanka,&quot; says Kaucký, but added to be on the safe side: &quot;But I know that from the newspaper.&quot;
And jokingly: &quot;I&#39;ll probably have to take a language course.&quot;
The &quot;golf hole&quot; is then correctly deciphered as the Blanka tunnel not only by matador Karel Březina, but also by environmental councilor Lukáš Plachý.
However, both social democrats also know who the term Voldemort stands for and Lukáš Plachý even has an inkling of where this figure can be found and therefore also what it means to &quot;go to the pastry shop&quot;.
