Defense Minister Alexandr Vondra and Army General Vlastimil Picek not exempt.
This is the only way to halfway justify the considerable annual consumption of sixty kilometers of fuses.
By the way, this length corresponds to 25,000 detonations.
But even so, these army stocks would last for more than ten years.
But if the old rule of experts still applies, that two meters of fuse is completely sufficient for the training of every new professional soldier, then with these new purchases the army has a reassuring stock for the already existing ones - also in view of the increased needs of the engineer and special units mentioned 225 years created.
Soldiers from the rapid deployment brigade recently complained to Defense Minister Vondra that they were almost out of cartridges for handguns, so that target practice is severely restricted due to the lack of funds.
