Defense Ministry spokesman Jan Pejšek justified the purchase of hundreds of kilometers of fuse by saying that the army would have stocked up on this &quot;ammunition&quot; for at least ten years.
However, Jan Děcký from the STV Group only speaks of a four-year service life for the fuses and police and army pyrotechnicians only two years.
&quot;With perfect storage, the four years mentioned are probably also possible,&quot; admits one of them, who, however, wishes to remain anonymous so as not to be accused of criticizing the army as a soldier.
At the end of its service life, all ammunition must be thoroughly tested to ensure that it is still reliable and does not endanger the lives of soldiers.
