&quot;They cost us 60 percent less than last year&#39;s delivery of 244 kilometers,&quot; spokesman Pejšek tells us about the position of the Defense Ministry&#39;s buyers.
Just for comparison: The annual use of fuses by police pyrotechnicians who liquidate ammunition from the Second World War or the Soviet brother army has barely exceeded 1,500 meters for several years.
