In the opera category, Berg&#39;s &quot;Lulu&quot; by the Royal Opera House Orchestra; Adolf Hasse&#39;s &quot;Marc Antonio e Cleopatra&quot; by Ars Lyrica Houston; Kaija Saariaho&#39;s &quot;L&#39;Amour de Loin&quot; by the Deutsches Symphonie-Orchester Berlin; Rodion Shchedrin&#39;s &quot;The Enchanted Wanderer&quot; by the Mariinsky Theater Orchestra and Chorus; and Arthur Sullivan&#39;s &quot;Ivanhoe&quot; by the BBC National Orchestra of Wales.
As composers, Pärt for Symphony No. 4, Daugherty for &quot;Deus Ex Machina&quot;, Hans Werner Henze for &quot;Appassionatamente Plus&quot;, Magnus Lindberg for &quot;Graffiti&quot; and Shchedrin for &quot;The Enchanted Wanderer&quot; were nominated for a Grammy.
Pärt&#39;s Symphony No. 4 was premiered and recorded on January 4 at Disney Hall by the LA Philharmonic conducted by Esa-Pekka Salonen.
