Mosque in Temecula wins planning committee approval
The construction of a mosque in Temecula received unanimous approval from the local planning committee after a five-hour, often heated, public hearing.
Critics accused the project of promoting both terrorism and traffic congestion.
However, according to a statement by the commission on Wednesday evening, the new religious center complies with local regulations and will be an aesthetic eye-catcher.
